---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="The Magic — Formic Platform"
  description="PLC reliability meets software intelligence. Cortex and Core — the hybrid platform behind every Formic system."
  ogTitle="The Magic — Formic Platform"
  ogDescription="Cortex and Core — PLC reliability with software intelligence."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/magic" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>The Magic
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">The Magic</div>
    <h1>PLC reliability.<br><em>Software intelligence.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Formic's hybrid architecture pairs deterministic industrial control with a modern software layer. Your automation gets smarter over time, never obsolete — and your maintenance team never has to choose between modern features and proven reliability.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">Architecture</div>
      <h2>Two layers, <em>one system</em>.</h2>
      <p>Most automation platforms force a tradeoff: rock-solid PLC control with no software smarts, or modern software on top of brittle integration. Formic doesn't make you choose. Cortex and Core run together as one system, with each layer doing what it does best.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li><strong>Cortex</strong> — software intelligence for fleet management, analytics, and operator UX</li>
        <li><strong>Core</strong> — deterministic, safety-rated PLC motion control on industrial hardware</li>
        <li>Same building blocks across every deployment, every customer, every site</li>
        <li>Continuous feature releases to Cortex without touching Core's reliability</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Hybrid platform diagram concept" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Hybrid platform</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-9787.jpg" alt="Cortex software dashboard concept" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Cortex · The intelligence layer</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Cortex</div>
      <h2>The software brain across <em>every Formic system</em>.</h2>
      <p>Cortex is the intelligence layer that ties every cell, line, and site together — fleet visibility, remote diagnostics, real-time analytics, and continuous OTA upgrades. Your operators and our support engineers see the same live data, everywhere.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Real-time OEE, throughput, and cycle-time analytics</li>
        <li>Encrypted remote diagnostics with full root-cause tooling</li>
        <li>Operator-friendly bilingual HMI on every machine</li>
        <li>Continuous, backward-compatible feature releases</li>
        <li>Integration-ready APIs for MES and ERP</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">See Cortex live →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Core</div>
      <h2>Industrial-grade control, <em>standardized</em>.</h2>
      <p>Core delivers deterministic, safety-rated PLC motion on proven industrial hardware. The same reliability your maintenance team already knows — KUKA, ABB, FANUC, Doosan, Rockwell, Siemens — now with software visibility on top.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Hard-real-time PLC motion control (Rockwell Automation, Siemens)</li>
        <li>Standardized "Lego-block" modular architecture across every deployment</li>
        <li>KUKA, ABB, FANUC, Doosan robots — unified under one OS</li>
        <li>Safety-rated stops, light curtains, and area scanners as standard</li>
        <li>Backward compatibility maintained across every fleet release</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Talk to engineering →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0095.jpg" alt="Core control layer in a Formic cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Core · The control layer</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey full">
  <div class="si" style="text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="display:inline-block">Together</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(36px,4vw,60px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1.05;color:var(--white);margin:14px auto 22px;max-width:720px">Reliability where you need it,<br><em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">intelligence where you want it</em>.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:17px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.7;color:rgba(240,245,241,.65);max-width:680px;margin:0 auto">Hybrid is the only architecture that scales across mid-market manufacturing without forcing tradeoffs between safety, modernization, and cost. Every Formic system runs both layers — that's the magic.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>One platform.<br><em>Every Formic system.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get a Demo</a>
    <a href="/" class="btn-ctawh">Back to Home</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
